/* Importance */ Removed section where it is claimed that wave function collapse is no different from other (unitary) interactions. Wave function collapse remains an open issue in quantum mechanics, and the proposed section mentioning decoherence theory does by no means provide an answer to the measurement problem. In any case, the act of measurement cannot be simply be explained by (unitary) interaction alone.
